---
/**
 * streaming-event-driven · exactly-once-kafka-deep-dive · Figure 2 — the broker's
 * sequence-number verdict (Level 1).
 *
 * Verbatim from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). Marker refs (#arw)
 * resolve against the shared arrowhead <defs> emitted once in the MDX body.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Broker decision on incoming sequence number versus last accepted: less-or-equal is a duplicate ACKed but discarded; one greater is accepted; more than one greater is a gap rejected with OutOfOrderSequence"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect x="220" y="14" width="160" height="38" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#7a1f12"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="32"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">broker compares seq vs last</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="46" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >per (PID, partition)</text
            >
            <!-- three branches -->
            <rect x="14" y="92" width="180" height="48" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="104"
                y="110"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">seq ≤ last → DUPLICATE</text
            >
            <text x="104" y="126" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >ACK producer, do NOT append</text
            >
            <rect x="210" y="92" width="180" height="48" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="110"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">seq = last+1 → ACCEPT</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="126" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >append, advance counter</text
            >
            <rect x="406" y="92" width="180" height="48" rx="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="496"
                y="110"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">seq &gt; last+1 → GAP</text
            >
            <text x="496" y="126" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >reject: OutOfOrderSequence</text
            >
            <g stroke="#6b675f">
                <line x1="260" y1="52" x2="120" y2="90" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
                <line x1="300" y1="52" x2="300" y2="90" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
                <line x1="340" y1="52" x2="480" y2="90" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            </g>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The retry vanishes (≤ last); the normal next batch advances (last+1); a hole is refused
        (&gt; last+1).
    </figcaption>
</figure>
